76561198113965360,Recommended,297470,23329467,"Posted: 1 June, 2016",all,Humerox,"If you're a hardcore crafter the buck stops here. Grind to your heart's delight. I put off getting this game and tried Albion, Elder Scrolls, Shroud of the Avatar, Wurm...none of them did me any good. I'm an old school player, and enjoy open world/sandbox play with no questing or linear gameplay. This game is about as sandbox as it gets. I'm already addicted! If you like action MMO's this is not up your alley, but if you like unlimited freedom and a complex crafting game with a little combat thrown in, this one's for you.Also, anyone reviewing this game with less than a couple hours played hasn't even finished the tutorial and has no business commenting on it. Yes the tutorial takes that long - longer actually. This game is NOT for those who want instant gratification and think graphics make a game. The graphics are more than good, they're just not cutting edge. If that's what you want spend your money elsewhere.This game makes you work hard for everything you do. THAT's the challenge. Can you handle it?"
,Recommended,297470,22536257,"Posted: 20 April, 2016",all,WickedPuppy,"I played this game years ago when it first came out and all you could do was terraform the landscape. It quickly lost my attention. I picked it up when it came out on Steam and outside of the low server population, this is a must have game for those into survival/building games. If you like crafting, gathering supplies, exploring, and building structures you will find plenty to do. You can build roads, terraform the landscape, farm the land, cut down trees, build everything in game, and all of this is visible to other players. Everything in game ages and/or gains xp. That Reverant that killed you an hour ago, stole your clothes and shovel from your corpse and now struts around with those items on him, taunting you to come kill him to get it back.Amazingly this game is ran by a single developer; yet, has more thought and work done to it then most MMO's on the market today. If you are looking for a game where twitchy fingers wins the day, this is not that game. This is a survival game, with what could be an attempt at a Trading simulation game. Although there are many aspects of the game that remain unpolished, it is extremely playable and stable, and simple in many regards.The learning curve is somewhere in between WoW and EVE online. It does not appear to have the same depth as EVE Online, but give this game a full staff of developers and it could easily come close over time. The next UO, probably. The next WoW, possibly. It just would depend which direction it went. Of course, neither matter if the graphics do not keep up.The immediate downfall of the game is that the communications systems in game are horrible and most people are into solo gameplay. A new person joining the game is dropped into the middle of a huge map (literally can take hours to travel from one part to another). The server population is so low that I have only seen other players when I requested to meet them in person and travelled to their location. However, everyone is extremely nice and friendly. If the developer moved in the direction of an EVE economy I think this game would have serious staying power, and be able to expand rapidly. However, if one cannot view at distances items for sale, then one might as well be playing a solo or cooperative game, not an MMO. This game needs some way to allow a greater sense of where you as an individual, as a tribe stand in relation to others.Overall, I recommend this game, with the reservations noted above."
76561198378105185,Recommended,297470,31098487,Posted: 12 April,all,Derwood Smallberries,"Hello!I am writing this review to let everyone know just how much I like this game.AND It seems very odd to me that Xsyon is so underrated and unknown!This game has so much to offer a player like me. I am older, in my 60's but have played mmo's since they first came out.I have played all the major old school mmo's like Everquest, and many of the newer class of games like Allods, terra and the like. Im a huge fan of seamless 3d environments, and really like the feel of Xsyon.One thing I really like, is that I don't have to rush to the ""end"" here. With so many skills to work with and so many things to craft and build, I reckon i'll be here for years.Oh, and speaking of building, you should see the amazing things people build in this game! I have been on a walk about all over, and have seen things like full sized castles, indoor swimming pools, paddocks for animals, and cool little villages. I have not don't much building yet but from what i gather from players, its a module style building system, with things like wall, truss, and roof parts that you can put together in many different combos. Plenty of styles to choose from as well.I've done a fair bit of crafting so far and it is pretty typical of other games. I do like the way this game provides the baski tools you need to give it a go. I learned the hard way that the first thing you should do with your starter tools is make more starter tools!  I reckon my next project will be to make me some armour.The community in this game is true blue. Always helpful and willing to keep ya going. Like, they warned me not to mess with ""revs"" yet till I was a bit more experienced. Once I found them at an abandoned homestead, I know what they meant. Imagine sick starkers running around trying to kill you and you have the picture. Most had twice the hit points I had and I had to run away not to die. I have'nt even tried animals yet, but I'm sure that day will come.All in all, this game may not be your cuppa, but if you enjoy a good community, and time to make your mark, then you are gonna love this game. Please don't take my word for it though, just go all in and try it mate!  You won't regret it!"
,Recommended,297470,32842047,Posted: 26 June,all,legend552,"Ok, so this game gets a lot more flak than it deserves. It IS understandable though why most people wouldn't enjoy it. It's a game that take a LOT of time to get use to, and what most people don't know is the true purpose of this game. It was meant to be a role playing game that is player driven, with quests that players created, and players would specialize in 1-2 skills and be that way. The gameplay is a slow progression, and I mean slow, but is pretty nice with friends. I have only played it with one friend, and he's really endowed into this game, and I am pretty into it as well. The theming is great, as is the art and concept of the tools. However, the combat is a different story. The combat is twitch based, which is great for PvP, as I play on the PvP server (There is a PvP and PvE server). However, it's not that way with enemies such as creatures. The creatures attack way too fast, and do way too much damage for how fast they attack. Some enemies called Revenants use the Twitch based combat, but as I said, they attack with too much damage for how fast they swing. Once you get used to the combat, you'll be able to progress from small critters to mediocre critters, to medium creatures and critters, and large/deadly critters/creatures. I level them by their HP and Attack strength. The building system is phenominal, you're able to create these pretty nice structures, however you'll need to increase your skills to build better things, as expected. The cooking system is great, the cookable objects have flavors which you need to balance out to make a fully nutritious food item without penalties (Food effectiveness reduction). As said though, you will need dedication for some skills, such as some craft skills, as you'll need to effectively grind EXP manually, which can be time consuming, so you'll need some time to kill. If you have a friend, it'll be great. You can adventure together, and you can create quests together. The tutorial is pretty time consuming, and if you want better help and explanations, you should ask people in the chat. All in all, great game, it's ashame but partially understandable the amount of flak it has been recieving."
