76561198122944962,Recommended,297470,31547112,Posted: 4 May,all,Alyngwen Clævyan,"TL;DR: Like grindy games? Play. Don’t like grindy games? Don’t play.As I stand at the edge of a small peninsula located between two waterfalls that cascade down into the valley below I marvel at the beauty of the – for a nooby rather dangerous –surroundings of the aptly named two-man community “Twin Fall Town”.The idyllic spot – that was chosen for beauty rather than functionality – is, to say the least, a bit of a challenge, and a struggle at most. Wild bears, hostile hounds, over-sized racoons (maybe the radiation has something to do with that?), and savage coyotes often interrupt the flow of our day while we’re trying – after 19+ hours in-game – to still finish the crude barricade around our soon-to-be-town, that will hopefully one day save our lives a few times in the future. For now, however, it is a long and slow battle against nature where we are the unwelcome guests.Welcome to Xsyon; an Early Access Post-Apocalyptic Open-World Online Survival game with Role-Playing elements. That’s a whole mouthful and the time it takes to pronounce this gives you a rough idea of the length of the game.Before you read any further, however: if you don’t appreciate a (very rewarding) grind-game: close the tab, delete this game from your wish list and move on.If you do enjoy a slow-paced game in a huge open world with survival, building, crafting, and battling the elements (or other players on the PvP server) whilst having tons of recipes to discover and stats to improve – and most important of all; you don’t mind grinding it full-on – than look no further: this is the game for you.Xsyon is still in early access which does mean you’ll have to deal with the odd bugs – such as not being able to run up a steep hill, while a bear or racoon easily walks up a vertical waterfall (obviously, a horizontal waterfall is called a river) – and updates are not released very often as it is being made by a small team.But the game is enjoyable! The amount of content it already has (which seems to be expanding a lot over the next few months) is astonishing. The grind – although at times you really feel you should do something else in between before you start going crazy – is actually quite spot on; you don’t build a village in a day, you don’t learn all recipes in three hours, and you don’t catch a fish every time you throw out your line, right?If you’re reading this I’m assuming you’ve got some affinity with survival games, too, so you’ll be familiar with the hunger/thirst aspect of this genre. Whereas many survival games (I’m looking at you, The Black Death) have a hunger-rate that goes down faster than a fat kid on a seesaw, Xsyon seems to have found a rather good balance, and a nice addition is that you shouldn’t “fill up” on food or water until your bar is at 100% as this will affect your character (and not in a good way).Also the day/night cycle takes a lot longer than in many other (early access) survival games. Beyond Despair is a dark setting anyway, but the nights seem to last forever; The Black Death (sorry, I’m still a huge fan of this game) has finally added a day/night cycle to their game, too, which is long and pitch-black; Xsyon has 9-hour in-game days. That’s pretty long, and in my opinion enjoyable, too, because of the game’s “grindy-ness”. You really need that time to scavenge for resources and you’d get really cranky if every 20 minutes the world goes dark for a friggin’ hour.In other words; Xsyon most definitely has added the survival aspect, but has implemented it in such a delicate way that you at some point think: “It’s been a while; my character might be a bit hungry, let’s break the grind and go fishing instead.” rather than “I’d like to go to [location] but I have to eat 15 apples, 2 loaves of bread and a basket of sour grapes and then scavenge for food first before I… Oh now it’s dark again; better wait till morning.”I do recommend playing with a friend if you want to start a tribe of your own, or you may want to join an existing tribe before setting off on your own so you can level up your skills first. In my experience the players on PvE (Peaceful) are very polite and helpful and will give new players some basic free gifts just to help them on their way (a few pouches and a basket, which you can’t make at the start of the game, are very welcome gifts).Xsyon may not be the most beautiful game on the market (graphically), the game needs performance updates as at times it runs quite poorly in forests, and some of the character’s movements are a bit wonky at times (running can be almost “slow-motion-like” on certain surfaces, while walking anywhere seems as if your character’s legs have been placed in spleens and he/she was then refused to use crutches), but none of this matters as you slowly grind away trying to make something of your life in the wilderness before winter arrives and you’re going to be royally [......]."
76561198078723020,Recommended,297470,26114348,"Posted: 19 October, 2016",all,the_bill_grahams,"i have just started playing and have found the small community to be very helpful.  I will say the jury is still out on wheather i think its worth buying.. i am still playing it.  It is very difficult to get started, i was lucky and an experienced player came from a far distance and spent over an hour with me teaching me the fundamentals.  he probably saved me many hours of trying to figure it out myself, as the tutorial was not very helpful.I am now having a problem that im sure will stop a lot of new players from playing.  the came is a crafting, building survival game.  you start with a basic set of tools to do the crafting.  these tools wear out in a little while.  you have receies to make some of them but not all.  im at a point where my two of my main crafting tools have worn out and i cant make new ones because i dont have the receipe.  I have found a tribe ldr that is willing to give me tools if i join his tribe (he might give them even if i didnt join).  This problem nearly caused me to give up playing because you cant play without the tools.  all the basic tool receipes should be there, and make you scavenge or harvest the materials to make them.  more advanced tools could be hard to get but not beginner tools.I do thank all the experienced players for all their help when i ask questions in chat."
