hoices for clothing weapons and tool styles each needing different resources- limited grinding for resources or construction - moderate to average on skills high level skills actually making you work for them instead of being given to you.- good blends of skill selection - starting kits tailored to your choices at start up - select axe as your weapon you get a axe select pick you get a pick ect ect - no starting short sword and shield generic kit- solid community willing to talk and helpcons-the games a bit confusing out of the gate - and needs a new tutorial / upgraded wiki majorly but after a week its not bad- limited decorations for inside a house - outside a house plenty of choices but not allot of furniture rugs ect- no current taming system - its in the works and I will remove this once its in- combat is a bit hit and miss atm - you can kill most small animals (squirels hampsters bunnys) but they tend to run from you and the actual click to hit system is a bit sensative meaning you have to hit a small animal running through the grassand its a bit difficult at times - they are supposed to be increaseing the hit detection area on small animals to remedy this and will be removed when added- no ranged combat - only melee weapons sorry- limited pvp - as the core game everyone uses is main job atm pvp feels a bit left out and the pvp server has very few people spaced far out on it.the pro/con - this is the section that could go either way for you - some like these options some don't - and some I just have mixed feelings toward-few to no trolls - might not be a big deal to you but I have a job / family / and life away from computer so knowing I won't have to log in and deal with some angry child blowing up half my town cause his parents told him he couldn't go out with friends is major bonus for me- low player base - this is a game of hundreds to thousands not hundreds of thousands it is ment to be a small market game catering to the people who enjoy this kind of game not to the masses - to me this is big as finding a unique game mmo not just a mini run your own server game is a big pro for me as I feel like I know those around me at same time people get a bit quiet at times which can be a turn off for others- many features have not been implamented - the current game is solid but allot of those I would really like features are coming but not yet in the game - while I can't wait for them to get in game I also can't wait. . . . seriously I want them now lolsso would I buy this game again? Yes - Will I play this game hard core for years? probably off and on yes like any sandbox this is a game you will keep coming back to once you have had your fill and keep enjoying it"
