76561198038128323,Recommended,297470,22900806,"Posted: 10 May, 2016",all,Slurpiderp,"New Xsyon player here, and here is what I think of this game in just seven hours.  I will update this review as I continue to work in the game.Simple question: ""Should I buy this game?""General answer: if you like sandbox free-to-do-as-you-please types, then yes.  It's worth the investment.  You can tell a lot of effort has been put into this game, though it's fairly underdeveloped.  The developer still seems actively involved in the community, but the community is lacking.  Nice people, just few of them on.  Expect to solo while you learn, and that's totally fine.This game is crafting heavy, but it takes a lot of time (and boring clicking and clicking and clicking) to get what you want done.  I mean a lot of time!  Not even so much that it's a lot of time, but that it's super slow-going, and very little instruction in-game, with a fairly generic tutorial.To have the best chance to start enjoying this game, I advise you make basket making your primary starting hobby.  This will help you get to the baskets you'll need to start developing resources without spending ten hours figuring out that you need to do this, and five more leveling it by farming grass and making thread and so on.  Once you have baskets, you're golden to start working the land.My advice further:  Safely navigate around the lake.  Find an area off the lake that has trees, rocks, and access to the lake.  Set up a tribe.  Start developing your totem area (aka learning your crafts).  Get to know the ten players in the game at any given time.  Eventually join their tribe just so you have something to build onto.  Or keep developing your own.By doing this, you will be in a safe zone for learning the basics.  You will be near a source of food (fishing), ability to develop tools and masonry, have baskets to store your stuff while you get started, and eventually be strong enough to get going on your own adventure or join up with others on a mmo adventure.Cons:  This game is still clunky.  Poor in-game tools.  Poor explanations.  Poor interface that is arduous and annoying.  Not intuitive at all.  But as you get the hang of it, it starts to make sense and works out.  But it's still clunky as all getout.  I imagine the developer is still trying to get this thing rolling, but it's been in dev for going on ten years.  Don't expect much.  Get it for what it is and play it accordingly.  It's worth that much.  Maybe by 2050, he will have it working as fluidly as minecraft."
