76561198001589085,Recommended,297470,15737490,"Posted: 8 May, 2015",all,Manron,"I'm really enjoying this game for the reasons that others downvote it for.  I'd always chose a subscribtion based game over a free to play one, as free to play games usually are the greater rip-off if you really want to get into them. Almost all games i know of that are advertised for as being ""free"" turn out to be pay to win after a while. Here you buy the game, pay the monthly fee (you dont even have to do this if you dont mind the skillcap), and that's it.Keep in mind this is a sandbox, not a theme park. This game is what you make of it and strongly encourages team play. If you like grinding for skills and crafting, you can do it. If you like exploring and hunting, you can do it. It's also totally valid to just fish, farm and cook and never leave your homestead. It's totally up to you.You wont start with all off the games posibillities revealed to you, you have to work on your skills and talents to find out what you REALLY can do.Speaking of skills, what you do is what you get, chopping wood will get you logging skill, preparing meals will raise your cooking, clubbing rats will get your fighting skills up. On top of that you can spend some skillpoints rewarded for active gameplay to speed up the process. That's a brilliant concept to me.About limited character customization... that's just not true. There are so many different armor and cloth pieces you can wear, i dont even dare to guess a number, it's hundreds at least.This game is tagged 'Early Access' not for being new but for being in constant developement. It may not be what you expect from a 'Early Access' game, but this one at least is totally playable and enjoyable with a huge area to explore and countless options for crafting and building on two persistent servers. This isnt vaporware like all those other early access games that never leave alpha or are abandoned by the devs after a year or two.About the graphics: I cant stress how much i hate the korean manga style graphics of all the WoW copy games that are out there. This games graphics may not be state of the art, but at least it's very solid with the animations and environment and get's the job done pretty well.Oh, and no magic! No 300 different buttons for this spell and that buff, attack combo here and there and such nonsense. Buffs/debuffs come from food and environmental conditions. that's it. Very refreshing approach!Speaking of combat, it's non target free for all. Swing your weapon and make sure the stuff you want to hit is where the weapon is moving to. That's how combat is done!Not click a target, then have some keyboard macro spit out your favourite attack combo with fireballs and sparks and flashy things until the target is dead. Bleh...so TLDR, this is a special game for special people. love it or hate it, but for the correct reasons."
