76561198034177353,Recommended,297470,15120709,"Posted: 29 March, 2015",all,Patty O'Furniture,"Well, what can I say. This game is the best I've seen of the open world variety in quite a while. Real gamers don't want to hear this, but to have a clue what you are doing, just do the dang tutorial. But if you don't, and have to ask questions, most of the players I've come across are willing to help...on the PVE server that is. Yes, 2 Servers, PvP and PvE, so if you want to peacefully go out, and build your homestead, without worrying about that guy across the river taking your hard earned grass stack(grass, not weed) after he bonks you on the head, then you have a server to play on.About the gameplay, I myself find it to be very similar to WoW, but without the NPC's. Crafting it rather well thought out, and building has it's quirks at times, but it works, and it works well.I hunt for games like this, and like I have said, it's the best I've seen in a while.It is a big help that there are guides(admin) that DO help, run events, and keep you updated as to scheduled patches and updates. They tell you when new things are on the test server, so you KNOW, because other players go check, that new content is soon to be available.All in all, I give this game a 9/10. Few minor bugs that are irritating, but in no way take away from the fun."
